Create OPCUA IoT Gateway
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click on "Data-Collector" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select "Kepware".
4
Move to "Create IoT Gateway".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
Select a Kepware Channel and click on it to expand its menu.
6
Choose "OPCUA Server".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Click the "Create" button and select the type of IoT Gateway you wish to create.
Select "IoT Gateway for OPCUA (reading)" if you want all tags contained in this
device to be exposed to the OPCUA Server in read-only mode. Instead, select "IoT
Gateway for OPCUA (write)" if you want the tags contained in this device to be
writable on the OPCUA Server.
8
Select the "Choose tags" checkbox if you want to choose only specific tags.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
Click on the little "arrow" on the left to expand the folder and tick all the tags (or
folders) you want to use.
10
Click the "greater than" button between "Channel" and "IoT Gateway", after you
finished choosing the tags (or folders) you need.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
Click the "Create IoT Gateway" button to complete the operation.
